{"title_page": "Hubert Kusz", "text_new": "{{short description|Polish association football player}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name           = Hubert Kusz\n| image          = \n| image_size     = \n| caption        = \n| fullname       = Hubert Kusz\n| birth_date     = {{Birth date |1928|9|21|df=y}} <ref>{{cite web|url=http://lechia.gda.pl/osoba/1499/|title=Hubert Kusz|website=lechia.gda.pl}}</ref>\n| birth_place    = [[Chorz\u00f3w]], Poland\n| death_date  = {{death date and age|2017|8|4|1928|9|21|df=y}} \n| death_place = [[Bydgoszcz]], Poland\n| height         = 170cm\n|       position = [[Defender (association football)|Defender]]\n| youthyears1    = 1942\u201346\n| youthclubs1    = [[AKS Chorz\u00f3w]]\n| years1         = 1946\u201348\n| clubs1         = [[Polonia \u015awidnica]]\n| caps1          = \n| goals1         = \n| years2         = 1949\u201360\n| clubs2         = [[Lechia Gda\u0144sk]]\n| caps2          = 174\n| goals2         = 2\n}}\n\n'''Hubert Kusz''' (21 September 1928 \u2013 4 August 2017) was a Polish footballer who played as a [[Defender (association football)|defender]]. He spent more than 10 years of his professional career playing for [[Lechia Gda\u0144sk]].\n\n==Biography==\nBorn in Chorz\u00f3w Kusz starting playing football for his local team [[AKS Chorz\u00f3w]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://lechiahistoria.pl/tag/hubert-kusz/|title=Hubert Kusz|website=lechiahistoria.pl}}</ref> After a few seasons of playing with [[Polonia \u015awidnica]] Kusz joined [[Lechia Gda\u0144sk]], a decision partly made due to knowing Lechia player [[Roman Rogocz]] from his time at AKS Chorz\u00f3w.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://lechiahistoria.pl/2018/09/21/hubert-kusz/|title=Hubert Kusz 2|website=lechiahistoria.pl}}</ref> He made his Lechia debut on 24 April 1949 against [[Warta Pozna\u0144]]. Kusz played in what was known as the golden period in Lechia's early history, playing in Lechia's [[Polish Cup]] final defeat in 1955<ref>{{cite web|url=http://lechia.pl/historia-25|title=Lechia Gda\u0144sk Historia|website=lechia.pl}}</ref> and playing 18 times in the 1956 season when Lechia finished in 3rd place,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hppn.pl/liga/sezon-po-sezonie/55,sezon-1956/145,I-liga/tabela|title=Tabela - 1956|website=hppn.pl}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://lechia.net/mecze-lechii-od-1945/player/109-1956-i-liga/1-lechia-gdask/879-hubert-kusz/|title=1956 I Liga|website=lechia.net}}</ref> the team's greatest league achievement until it was equaled in 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://lechia.pl/aktualnosci/lechia-gdansk-z-brazowym-medalem-mistrzostw-polski-15710|title=LECHIA GDA\u0143SK Z BR\u0104ZOWYM MEDALEM MISTRZOSTW POLSKI!|website=lechia.pl}}</ref> After that historic season Lechia finished the next few seasons until Kusz's retirement in mid-table positions. In total Kusz made 182 appearances and scoring 2 goals for Lechia, retiring in 1960.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://lechia.net/statystyki/wystepy|title=Wyst\u0119py|website=lechia.net}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://lechia.net/component/joomleague/player/105-1960-i-liga/1-lechia-gdask/879-hubert-kusz/|title=1960 I liga|website=lechia.net}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Hubert Kusz \u2013 Gwiazda Lechia Gda\u0144sk.JPG|thumb|250px|Hubert Kusz's star on the \"Avenue of Stars\"]]\nIn 2011 Kusz was awarded the [[Cross of Merit (Poland)|Cross of Merit]] for achievements in football and its popularization.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.prezydent.pl/archiwum-bronislawa-komorowskiego/aktualnosci/ordery-i-odznaczenia/art,997,odznaczenia-panstwowe-dla-zasluzonych-pilkarzy-lechii-gdansk.html|title=Odznaczenia pa\u0144stwowe dla zas\u0142u\u017conych pi\u0142karzy Lechii Gda\u0144sk|website=prezydent.pl}}</ref> The same year he was honoured with a star on Lechia's \"Avenue of Stars\", a way the club has commemorated Lechia Gda\u0144sk legends.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nekrologi.net/nekrologi/hubert-kusz/50872896|title=Hubert Kusz 2|website=nekrologi.net}}</ref>\n\nKusz died in [[Bydgoszcz]] on 4 August 2017 aged 89, with his funeral taking place on 9 August.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://lechiahistoria.pl/2018/09/21/hubert-kusz/|title=Hubert Kusz : Nekrologi|website=lechiahistoria.pl}}</ref>\n\n==Awards==\n*2011: Gold [[Cross of Merit (Poland)|Cross of Merit]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Kusz, Hubert}}\n[[Category:1928 births]]\n[[Category:2017 deaths]]\n[[Category:AKS Chorz\u00f3w players]]\n[[Category:Polonia \u015awidnica players]]\n[[Category:Lechia Gda\u0144sk players]]\n[[Category:Polish footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football defenders]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Polish association football player}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name           = Hubert Kusz\n| image          = \n| image_size     = \n| caption        = \n| fullname       = Hubert Kusz\n| birth_date     = {{Birth date |1928|9|21|df=y}} <ref>{{cite web|url=http://lechia.gda.pl/osoba/1499/|title=Hubert Kusz|website=lechia.gda.pl}}</ref>\n| birth_place    = [[Chorz\u00f3w]], Poland\n| death_date  = {{death date and age|2017|8|4|1928|9|21|df=y}} \n| death_place = [[Bydgoszcz]], Poland\n| height         = 170cm\n|       position = [[Defender (association football)|Defender]]\n| youthyears1    = 1942\u201346\n| youthclubs1    = [[AKS Chorz\u00f3w]]\n| years1         = 1946\u201348\n| clubs1         = [[Polonia \u015awidnica]]\n| caps1          = \n| goals1         = \n| years2         = 1949\u201360\n| clubs2         = [[Lechia Gda\u0144sk]]\n| caps2          = 174\n| goals2         = 2\n}}\n\n'''Hubert Kusz''' (21 September 1928 \u2013 4 August 2017) was a Polish footballer who played as a [[Defender (association football)|defender]]. He spent more than 10 years of his professional career playing for [[Lechia Gda\u0144sk]].\n\n==Biography==\nBorn in Chorz\u00f3w Kusz starting playing football for his local team [[AKS Chorz\u00f3w]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://lechiahistoria.pl/tag/hubert-kusz/|title=Hubert Kusz|website=lechiahistoria.pl}}</ref> After a few seasons of playing with [[Polonia \u015awidnica]] Kusz joined [[Lechia Gda\u0144sk]], a decision partly made due to knowing Lechia player [[Roman Rogocz]] from his time at AKS Chorz\u00f3w.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://lechiahistoria.pl/2018/09/21/hubert-kusz/|title=Hubert Kusz 2|website=lechiahistoria.pl}}</ref> He made his Lechia debut on 24 April 1949 against [[Warta Pozna\u0144]]. Kusz played in what was known as the golden period in Lechia's early history, playing in Lechia's [[Polish Cup]] final defeat in 1955<ref>{{cite web|url=http://lechia.pl/historia-25|title=Lechia Gda\u0144sk Historia|website=lechia.pl}}</ref> and playing 18 times in the 1956 season when Lechia finished in 3rd place,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hppn.pl/liga/sezon-po-sezonie/55,sezon-1956/145,I-liga/tabela|title=Tabela - 1956|website=hppn.pl}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://lechia.net/mecze-lechii-od-1945/player/109-1956-i-liga/1-lechia-gdask/879-hubert-kusz/|title=1956 I Liga|website=lechia.net}}</ref> the teams greatest league achievement until it was equaled in 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://lechia.pl/aktualnosci/lechia-gdansk-z-brazowym-medalem-mistrzostw-polski-15710|title=LECHIA GDA\u0143SK Z BR\u0104ZOWYM MEDALEM MISTRZOSTW POLSKI!|website=lechia.pl}}</ref> After that historic season Lechia finished the next few seasons until Kusz's retirement in mid-table positions. In total Kusz made 182 appearances and scoring 2 goals for Lechia, retiring in 1960.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://lechia.net/statystyki/wystepy|title=Wyst\u0119py|website=lechia.net}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://lechia.net/component/joomleague/player/105-1960-i-liga/1-lechia-gdask/879-hubert-kusz/|title=1960 I liga|website=lechia.net}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Hubert Kusz \u2013 Gwiazda Lechia Gda\u0144sk.JPG|thumb|250px|Hubert Kusz's star on the \"Avenue of Stars\"]]\nIn 2011 Kusz was awarded the [[Cross of Merit (Poland)|Cross of Merit]] for achievements in football and its popularization.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.prezydent.pl/archiwum-bronislawa-komorowskiego/aktualnosci/ordery-i-odznaczenia/art,997,odznaczenia-panstwowe-dla-zasluzonych-pilkarzy-lechii-gdansk.html|title=Odznaczenia pa\u0144stwowe dla zas\u0142u\u017conych pi\u0142karzy Lechii Gda\u0144sk|website=prezydent.pl}}</ref> The same year he was honoured with a star on Lechia's \"Avenue of Stars\", a way the club has commemorated Lechia Gda\u0144sk legends.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nekrologi.net/nekrologi/hubert-kusz/50872896|title=Hubert Kusz 2|website=nekrologi.net}}</ref> \n\nKusz died in [[Bydgoszcz]] on 4 August 2017 aged 89, with his funeral taking place on 9 August.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://lechiahistoria.pl/2018/09/21/hubert-kusz/|title=Hubert Kusz : Nekrologi|website=lechiahistoria.pl}}</ref> \n\n==Awards==\n*2011: Gold [[Cross of Merit (Poland)|Cross of Merit]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Kusz, Hubert}}\n[[Category:1928 births]]\n[[Category:2017 deaths]]\n[[Category:AKS Chorz\u00f3w players]]\n[[Category:Polonia \u015awidnica players]]\n[[Category:Lechia Gda\u0144sk players]]\n[[Category:Polish footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football defenders]]\n", "name_user": "John of Reading", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eBiography:Typo/generalfixes, replaced: teams greatest \u2192 team's greatest", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hubert_Kusz"}
